":"about 1210","January 1229":"January 1229","1229":"1229","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Huddersfield, Yorkshire, England":"Huddersfield, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Bashall Eaves, Yorkshire, England":"Bashall Eaves, Yorkshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Matilda","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Mathilda","meanings":["Old German: Mighty battle maid"]}]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Yorkshire","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name from the county of Yorkshire."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":5,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":14,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Matilda of Yorkshire was born about 1210, in Yorkshire, England. She married Robert de Talbot II in January 1229, in Yorkshire, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died after 1236."},"et":{"about 1210–after 1236":"umbes 1210–pärast 1236","1205–1235":"1205–1235","–Male":"Surnud","1229–Male":"1229–Surnud","1230–1273":"1230–1273","1210–1236":"1210–1236","after 1236":"pärast 1236","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1236":"1236","1235":"1235","1224":"1224","1210":"1210","1230":"1230","1273":"1273","about 1210":"umbes 1210","January 1229":"jaanuar 1229","1229":"1229","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Huddersfield, Yorkshire, England":"Huddersfield, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bashall Eaves, Yorkshire, England":"Bashall Eaves, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1210–after 1236":"noin 1210–1236 jälkeen","1205–1235":"1205–1235","–Male":"Kuollut","1229–Male":"1229–Kuollut","1230–1273":"1230–1273","1210–1236":"1210–1236","after 1236":"1236 jälkeen","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1236":"1236","1235":"1235","1224":"1224","1210":"1210","1230":"1230","1273":"1273","about 1210":"noin 1210","January 1229":"tammikuu 1229","1229":"1229","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Huddersfield, Yorkshire, England":"Huddersfield, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bashall Eaves, Yorkshire, E